gomodel:SYNGO_988  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: α-actinin-2 is found abundantly in crude synaptosomal membrane (Fig. 2A)\nα-Actinin-2 protein is localized to excitatory synapses (Fig. 5)\nImmunogold labeling for α-actinin-2 in postsynaptic densities (Fig. 6)\nColocalization of α-actinin-2 with postsynaptic proteins by EM (Fig. 7).\n\n28/6/2017 Pim\n- ACTN2 is localized in membrane and cytosolic synape preparations (Fig.2).\n- ACTN2 is localized to exc. synapses as shown by co-localization with Glur1\n- ACTN2 is mainly located at PSD (membrane and cytoplasmic part) and on microfilaments (a.k.a actin) (Fig.6).\n- ACTN2 is colocalizing at the inner face of the PSD membrane with the NR1 subunit (Fig.7).. Experimental description: M&M and results section\nImmunoblots of rat brain membranes\nMale Sprague Dawley rats were used for EM\nCrude synaptosomal membrane fraction from rat cortex" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_988" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

